When mass transport plays a role in the reaction rate, the current of the reaction can be derived from the Koutecky–Levich equation, Eq. (2), in which jrr is the overall current of the reaction, jBV is the kinetic current and jmtl is the mass transport current.21jrr=1jBV+1jmtl\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
