Essentially, this equation represents the kinetic and mass transport currents as two parallel current pathways. The kinetic current is described by Butler–Volmer kinetics, as in Eq. (1) for the non-mass transport limited case. The mass transport current is described by Eq. (3), in which jmtl,a/c are the anodic and cathodic limiting mass transport current densities, respectively, e is the elementary charge and Vmt is the overpotential due to mass transport.3jmtlVmt=1-exp-neeVmtkT⋅1jmtl,a-1jmtl,c⋅exp-neeVmtkT-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
